---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalSection from '../components/LegalSection.astro';
import SectionDivider from '../components/SectionDivider.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'Effective 3 July 2026';

const description =
  'The terms governing use of the Hamdam app, Hamdam Plus subscription, and journal content, including health disclaimers.';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'TermsAndConditions',
  name: 'Hamdam Terms of Service',
  description,
  url: 'https://hamdam.com.au/terms',
  datePublished: '2026-07-03',
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'Ealia Azizollahi',
  },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Hamdam"
  description={description}
  lang="en"
  path="/terms"
  altPath="/fa/terms"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-[var(--container-reading)] px-6 pb-32 pt-24 sm:pt-[100px] print:pt-8">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl font-bold text-indigo sm:text-[56px]">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 font-serif text-sm italic text-indigo/60">{effectiveDate} &middot; ~8 minute read</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-4 font-serif text-lg leading-[1.7] text-indigo/90">
      <p>
        Hamdam is a reflection companion grounded in Persian poetic wisdom. These Terms cover
        your licence to use the app, the Hamdam Plus subscription, and how your journal content
        is treated.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's worth the eight minutes, especially Section 4. Hamdam offers gentle reflection, not
        medical or mental health advice, and that distinction matters for how you use it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <LegalSection heading="1. Acceptance">
      <p>
        By downloading, installing, or using Hamdam, you agree to these Terms. If you don't
        agree, don't use Hamdam.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="2. License">
      <p>
        Hamdam grants you a personal, non-transferable, revocable licence to use the app on
        Apple devices you own or control, obtained through the App Store. This licence doesn't
        extend to commercial use or redistribution of the app or its content.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="3. Hamdam Plus Subscription">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.1 Pricing</h3>
      <p>
        Pricing is set and displayed by Apple at the point of purchase. Current pricing is
        available on the App Store and is subject to change by Apple.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.2 Free trial</h3>
      <p>
        Monthly and Yearly subscriptions include a 7-day free trial for new subscribers. The
        trial converts to a paid subscription unless cancelled before it ends &mdash; see Section
        3.5 for cancellation instructions.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.3 Family Sharing</h3>
      <p>
        The Lifetime plan supports Family Sharing, for up to six members through Apple's Family
        Sharing. Monthly and Yearly plans are single-user.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.4 Auto-renewal</h3>
      <p>
        Monthly and Yearly plans auto-renew unless cancelled, at the then-current price, charged
        to your Apple ID. Manage or cancel renewal through your Apple ID subscription settings.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.5 Cancellation</h3>
      <p>
        Cancel anytime via Settings &rarr; your Apple ID &rarr; Subscriptions on your device.
        Cancelling stops the next renewal; you keep access until the end of the current billing
        period. There's no refund for the unused portion of a current period, subject to Apple's
        own refund policy.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">3.6 Price changes</h3>
      <p>
        Apple may adjust pricing. You'll be notified in advance via the App Store, per Apple's
        standard process. Continuing your subscription after that notification means you accept
        the change.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <SectionDivider />

    <div class="mt-14 rounded-[var(--radius-card)] bg-peach/20 p-6 shadow-card sm:p-8">
      <LegalSection heading="4. Health and Wellness Disclaimers">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.1 Not medical advice</h3>
        <p>
          Hamdam is a reflection companion, not medical, mental health, or wellness advice.
          Nothing in Hamdam substitutes for professional healthcare, mental health support,
          medical diagnosis, or treatment.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.2 Consult professionals</h3>
        <p>
          For medical questions, physical or mental health concerns, or health decisions,
          consult a qualified healthcare provider.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.3 Mental health crisis</h3>
        <p>If you or someone you know is in crisis or needs immediate mental health support:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>Australia: Lifeline, 13 11 14 (24/7)</li>
          <li>Australia emergency: 000</li>
          <li>International: contact your local crisis line or emergency services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Hamdam is not a substitute for crisis support.</p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.4 Body observations</h3>
        <p>
          Hamdam offers gentle observations about body signals &mdash; sleep, activity, cycle.
          These are contextual observations, not medical assessments or diagnoses.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.5 Fitness features</h3>
        <p>
          Fitness observations are contextual only. Consult your doctor before starting an
          exercise routine, changing your physical activity, or acting on any fitness
          observation.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.6 Cycle awareness</h3>
        <p>
          Cycle observations use your logged menstrual data only. They are not a substitute for
          medical cycle tracking, pregnancy prevention, pregnancy planning, or medical
          consultation.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">4.7 Reflection content</h3>
        <p>
          Reflections and observations are contemplative in nature. They are not therapy,
          counselling, or spiritual guidance for medical use.
        </p>
      </LegalSection>
    </div>

    <LegalSection heading="5. Cultural Content Attribution">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">5.1 Persian poetry sources</h3>
      <p>
        Verses from Hafez, Rumi, Saadi, Khayyam, and Parvin Etesami are in the public domain,
        sourced from the Ganjoor.net archive with attribution. Hamdam's curation and English
        translations, along with its cultural context and reflections, are &copy; Ealia
        Azizollahi.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">5.2 Your rights to Hamdam content</h3>
      <p>Content is for your personal use within the app only. No commercial redistribution, and no republishing without permission.</p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">5.3 Cultural sensitivity</h3>
      <p>
        Persian poetry references wine, love, and mystical imagery as literary and spiritual
        metaphor. These are historical Persian literary conventions, not endorsements of
        substance use.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="6. User Content">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">6.1 Journal entries</h3>
      <p>
        You own your journal entries. Hamdam holds no licence to your journal content, and you
        can delete any entry at any time. Your journal syncs only through your own iCloud
        account.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">6.2 No sharing</h3>
      <p>
        Hamdam does not share your journal content with anyone. There's no public feed and no
        social features.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="7. Prohibited Uses">
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
        <li>Reverse engineering the app</li>
        <li>Redistributing app content</li>
        <li>Commercial use of the app or its content</li>
        <li>Using Hamdam to harm yourself or others</li>
        <li>Using Hamdam in violation of applicable law</li>
      </ul>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="8. Termination">
      <p>
        You can stop using Hamdam anytime by uninstalling it. Hamdam may terminate your access
        for violating these Terms. For subscription cancellation, see Section 3.5.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="9. Warranty Disclaimers">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">9.1 As-is</h3>
      <p>
        Hamdam is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; without warranties of any kind, except where
        non-excludable guarantees under Australian Consumer Law apply.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">9.2 Australian Consumer Law</h3>
      <p>
        Nothing in these Terms excludes, restricts, or modifies any non-excludable right under
        Australian Consumer Law. Where the ACL implies a condition, warranty, or guarantee, our
        liability for breach is limited to the extent the law permits.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="10. Limitation of Liability">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">10.1 Standard limitations</h3>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent the law permits, Hamdam is not liable for indirect, incidental,
        special, or consequential damages.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">10.2 Non-excludable rights</h3>
      <p>Where the ACL grants a non-excludable right, that right applies and this limitation does not restrict it.</p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-indigo">10.3 Health-related limitations</h3>
      <p>
        Hamdam is not liable for decisions made based on reflections, observations, or content in
        the app. Health decisions are yours, made in consultation with qualified professionals.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="11. Indemnification">
      <p>
        You agree to indemnify Hamdam for claims arising from your misuse of the app or
        violation of these Terms, to the extent the law permits.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="12. Third-Party Services">
      <p>
        Hamdam uses Apple's HealthKit, EventKit, WeatherKit, iCloud, StoreKit, and Foundation
        Models frameworks. Apple's own terms and privacy policies apply to those services.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="13. Changes to These Terms">
      <p>
        If these Terms change materially, you'll be notified through an app update. Continuing
        to use Hamdam after a change means you accept the update. The effective date at the top
        of this page always reflects the current version.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="14. Governing Law and Jurisdiction">
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of Queensland, Australia. Australian Consumer Law
        applies where relevant. Disputes are subject to the jurisdiction of Queensland courts,
        unless the ACL provides otherwise.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="15. Intellectual Property">
      <p>
        The HAMDAM&trade; name, trade mark, and the Hamdam app (including the iOS app, watchOS
        app, and any related services), content (including curated Persian poetry selections,
        reflection prompts, and cultural moment content), and all associated intellectual
        property are owned by Seyed Valiallah Azizollahi.
      </p>
      <p>
        HAMDAM&trade; is the subject of a pending trade mark application with IP Australia (filed
        July 2026, Classes 9 and 42).
      </p>
      <p>
        You may not use the HAMDAM name, trade mark, or any associated intellectual property
        without prior written permission from the owner.
      </p>
      <p>
        Persian poetry featured within the application is sourced from public domain works by
        classical Persian poets (Hafez, Rumi, Saadi, Khayyam, and Parvin Etesami). Original
        Persian text is sourced from Ganjoor.net. Reflections, curation, and English translations
        (where applicable) are the original work of the Hamdam team.
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <LegalSection heading="16. Contact">
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:developer@hamdam.com.au" class="text-saffron-ink underline">developer@hamdam.com.au</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-indigo/70">
        Ealia Azizollahi (sole trader) &middot; ABN 74 389 481 503 &middot; Brisbane, Queensland,
        Australia
      </p>
    </LegalSection>

    <p class="mt-14 font-serif text-base text-indigo/70">
      See also our <a href="/privacy" class="text-saffron-ink underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
    </p>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  @media print {
    :global(header),
    :global(nav) {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
